What you need to know:

Todt had earlier in the morning launched the WRC Safari Rally Greening Legacy Project at Kasarani by planting the first of 19 million trees next to the one he planted two and a half years ago, now blooming fast, at the WRC Safari Rally headquarters.He noted that Kenya was in pole position to do much more environmental work as assistance from the UN-Habitat based in Nairobi is at its doorstep.